ENTRY       EC 2.5.1.77                 Enzyme
NAME        7,8-didemethyl-8-hydroxy-5-deazariboflavin synthase;
            FO synthase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     5-amino-6-(D-ribitylamino)uracil:4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate, 4-methylphenol transferase
REACTION    5-amino-6-(D-ribitylamino)uracil + 3-(4-hydroxyphenyl)pyruvate + 2 S-adenosyl-L-methionine + H2O = 7,8-didemethyl-8-hydroxy-5-deazariboflavin + 2 L-methionine + 2 5'-deoxyadenosine + oxalate + NH3 [RN:R09396]
ALL_REAC    R09396
SUBSTRATE   5-amino-6-(D-ribitylamino)uracil [CPD:C04732];
            3-(4-hydroxyphenyl)pyruvate [CPD:C01179];
            S-adenosyl-L-methionine [CPD:C00019];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     7,8-didemethyl-8-hydroxy-5-deazariboflavin [CPD:C19154];
            L-methionine [CPD:C00073];
            5'-deoxyadenosine [CPD:C05198];
            oxalate [CPD:C00209];
            NH3 [CPD:C00014]
COMMENT     Binds a [4Fe-4S] cluster. The cluster is coordinated by 3 cysteines and an exchangeable AdoMet molecule. The first stage of catalysis is reduction of the 2 AdoMet to produce 2 methionine and 2 5'-deoxyadenosin-5-yl radicals that extract a hydrogen from each of the substrates permitting the condensation of the two [1]. The overall reaction catalysed is the transfer of the hydroxybenzyl group from 4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate (HPP) to 5-amino-6-ribitylaminopyrimidine-2,4(1H,3H)-dione to form 7,8-didemethyl-8-hydroxy-5-deazariboflavin (FO). 7,8-Didemethyl-8-hydroxy-5-deazariboflavin is the chromophore of the hydride carrier coenzyme F420 [1].
